{
  "$schema": "../../../../schema/vector.schema.json",
  "id": "messaging.brc31.authrite-signature",
  "name": "BRC-31 Authrite Mutual Authentication Signatures",
  "brc": [
    "BRC-31"
  ],
  "version": "1.1.1",
  "reference_impl": "@bsv/sdk@2.1.0",
  "parity_class": "required",
  "notes": "BRC-31 uses BRC-43 key derivation with protocol=[2,'authrite message signature']. The keyID is '<nonce1> <nonce2>' (space-separated base64-encoded nonce strings). For the initialResponse, Bob signs (aliceNonce_bytes || bobNonce_bytes) with keyID='<aliceNonce> <bobNonce>' and counterparty=aliceIdentityKey. For general messages, the sender signs the payload bytes with the agreed nonce pair as keyID. All signatures are DER-encoded ECDSA produced deterministically via RFC6979. Identity keys: scalar=1 => 0279be667ef9dcbbac55a06295ce870b07029bfcdb2dce28d959f2815b16f81798, scalar=2 => 02c6047f9441ed7d6d3045406e95c07cd85c778e4b8cef3ca7abac09b95c709ee5, scalar=3 => 02f9308a019258c31049344f85f89d5229b531c845836f99b08601f113bce036f9, scalar=4 => 02e493dbf1c10d80f3581e4904930b1404cc6c13900ee0758474fa94abe8c4cd13. Vectors 1-4 are deprecated because their expected signatures were generated by an older SDK version and do not match the current deterministic RFC6979 output.",
